                        <div id="agenda-intro">
                          <h2>Introduction to Agenda</h2>
                          <div class="divide20"></div>
                          <h3>Agenda: Reportage of all committees (Video and Write Up)</h3>
                          <p>The IPC this year will be functioning in a slightly different manner. The double delegations have been introduced to ensure interdependent journalism, and in the IPC, there will be no one journalist doing all the work. The working is as such: Delegations will be split on both days that committee is held, i.e. Day 1 and Day 2. There will be no work on Day 3, though delegations must come to committee. Through chit-picking, the delegation will receive their committees on the first day. They will then split up and present one write-up each in the style of their news agency, as well as one video recording each of an interview taken with a delegate from the committee they are reporting on. On the second day, delegations will pick chits again, but this time, they will be picking chits with the names of different delegations, and those two delegations will have to switch committees. Chits will be picked until all delegations have switched agencies. It is up to the members of that delegation to choose which committee from the two they wish to cover on the second day. Once again, they will have to submit a write-up and a video. Awards will be given on an agency basis and not an individual delegate basis. </p>
